<p>The <code>@variables</code> property returns all level-scoped variables as iterable data.</p>

<h2>List All Variables</h2>
<pre>{open}users a="first" b="second" c="third"{close}
  {open}@first{close}
    Variables:
    {open}@variables{close}
      &lt;li&gt;{open}$name{close} = {open}$value{close}&lt;/li&gt;
    {open}/@variables{close}
  {open}/@first{close}
{open}/users{close}</pre>

<p>Result:</p>
{users a="first" b="second" c="third"}
  {@first}
    Variables:
    <ul>
    {@variables}
      <li>{$name} = {$value}</li>
    {/@variables}
    </ul>
  {/@first}
{/users}

<h2>Note</h2>
<p>Each item has <code>$name</code> (variable name) and <code>$value</code> (variable value). Useful for inspecting all level-scoped variables.</p>
